Program: Start the Week
Title: 14/12/2009
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/b00p87qw
Last Broadcast Date: Mon 14 Dec 2009
Tom Sutcliffe explores the pitfalls of the web, with Evgeny Morozov arguing that it's exploited by dictators, and Andrew Dalby gives his views on Wikipedia. Amanda Goodall decries the prevalence of the professional manager, and the art historian David Boyd Haycock talks about the 'crisis of brilliance' of the Young British Artists of the early 1900s. Show less